==English==
===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-gaze.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''gaze'''  (''plural:'' '''[[gazes]]''')
# A [[fix]]ed [[look]]; a look of eagerness, wonder, or admiration; a continued look of attention.
# {{archaic}}: The object gazed on.

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|gaz|e}}
# To fix the eyes in a steady and earnest look; to look with eagerness or curiosity, as in admiration, astonishment, or with studious attention.
#:''In fact, for Antonioni this '''gazing''' is probably the most fundamental of all cognitive activities ...''  (from [http://www.italian.ucla.edu/faculty/harrison/Essays/Antonioni.htm Thinking in the Absence of Image])
# To [[view]] with [[attention]].

